From: Sun Yuechi <sunyuechi@iscas.ac.cn>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] build: prefer home:sunyuechi:openruyi-test OBS repo for deps

Add the temporary OBS project as a dnf repo with priority=1
inside the openRuyi build container, so dependency installation
(buildcontainer-setup.sh bootstrap and install-deps.sh builddep) picks
packages from the temporary project whenever it publishes them, and falls
back to the image's stock openRuyi repos for everything else.

openRuyi downstream (2xxx); applies on top of 1002.

Signed-off-by: Sun Yuechi <sunyuechi@iscas.ac.cn>
---
 src/script/buildcontainer-setup.sh | 18 ++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/script/buildcontainer-setup.sh b/src/script/buildcontainer-setup.sh
--- a/src/script/buildcontainer-setup.sh
+++ b/src/script/buildcontainer-setup.sh
@@ -44,9 +44,27 @@ case "${CEPH_BASE_BRANCH}~${DISTRO_KIND}" in
     *~*openruyi*)
         # openRuyi ships a minimal OCI image (bash, dnf5, rpm, curl only).
         # Install the tools the container build itself needs (rpmbuild for the
         # spec-driven builddep, plus the usual fetch/archive helpers) before
         # handing off to install-deps.sh via install_container_deps.
+        # Prefer the temporary OBS project for any package it
+        # publishes (priority=1 beats the stock repos' default 99); packages
+        # it does not carry still come from the image's stock openRuyi repos.
+        # OBS-published RPMs are unsigned (gpgcheck=0), and an unpublished or
+        # unreachable project must not break CI (skip_if_unavailable=1).
+        cat > /etc/yum.repos.d/home_sunyuechi_openruyi-test.repo <<'REPO'
+[home_sunyuechi_openruyi-test]
+name=home:sunyuechi:openruyi-test (riscv64)
+baseurl=https://repo.build.openruyi.cn/home:/sunyuechi:/openruyi-test/riscv64/
+enabled=1
+gpgcheck=0
+priority=1
+skip_if_unavailable=1
+REPO
+        # Pull openruyi-release carrying macros.openruyi (%openruyi spec guard)
+        # from the temp repo before builddep parses the spec; no-op once the
+        # stock repos ship it.
+        dnf -y upgrade openruyi-release
         dnf install -y dnf5-plugins rpm-build python3 wget tar gzip /usr/bin/{rpmbuild,curl}
         install_container_deps
         dnf_clean
     ;;
